retweeted_text: CUYAHOGA: Outpatient visits for coronavirus more than tripled during the past three weeks. It’s critical that the residents of Cuyahoga County remain vigilant and do all they can to reduce their risk and exposure to coronavirus. We are continuing to monitor their data closely.

full_text: Until we can widely administer a vaccine for COVID-19, we need every tool at our disposal to help suppress the spread of the virus, including improving our ability to voluntarily isolate infected individuals.

Parents: This will help your children #LearnAtHome!⬇️

We are so grateful to #Ohio's PBS stations and everyone involved in making this happen. 

The educational programming starts on most stations in #Ohio TODAY! #InThisTogetherOhio

More info: https://t.co/iIDVCqRcRX https://t.co/gKdch8MzcR

full_text: Incredibly proud of the strength of our #NortheastOhio community. A small group in #Strongsville has launched a national movement, lighting up skies across the country to remind us we are #inthistogether. More on the first Unite The Night here: https://t.co/WBa2zDG04J

full_text: Today on #TVT (Thank-a-Vet Thursday) I'm honoring Northeast Ohio WWII Veteran Glenn Smith, who passed away last week at age 95. My office had the honor of presenting Glenn with his military service medals last year. Today we remember his life and thank him for serving our nation. https://t.co/HzvtmffraI

retweeted_text: Congratulations to @RepBenMcAdams & @RepAGonzalez on passage of their bipartisan Advancing Research to Prevent Suicide Act, #HR4704 on the House floor last night. APA supports HR 4704 because it directs @NSF to fund multidisciplinary research grants to study #suicide.

full_text: I sincerely believe that if we want to make a dent on preventing suicide, we need to be more proactive in finding the causes of suicide clusters and suicide contagions. Our children, our veterans, and our neighbors deserve action.

@RepAGonzalez is absolutely right. #USMCA will increase GDP by more than $68 billion and create 76,000 jobs in the U.S. auto industry. 

Ohio's workers and manufacturers have been waiting for Congress to ratify USMCA for more than a year. It's time for Congress to act. https://t.co/4r896LdEjd

full_text: Disappointing to see @SpeakerPelosi walk back her comments about passing #USMCA this year. USMCA means more jobs, higher wages and a stronger economy. We must put partisan politics aside, put our constituents and communities first, and pass USMCA into law. https://t.co/gZ3FyIu9e1

"Folks are moving to Singapore, Switzerland, the UK because of the [regulatory] clarity..." 

A growing worry in the open blockchain community: if the US won't support us, where should we go?

Thanks @RepAGonzalez for raising the flag on this issue.

full_text: It's absolutely critical that we keep our eye on the prize with #USMCA - this trade deal would remove barriers to trade and provide economic certainty for our farmers, small businesses and manufacturers. We need to pass #USMCAnow. https://t.co/daSe7VzB9Z

Too often the focus is on where we disagree, but I was proud to join my Republican colleague Rep. Anthony Gonzalez and visit his district in Ohio. I hope we set an example of bipartisanship b/c working together is key to getting things done.

Excited to welcome him to #TX32 soon! https://t.co/Ya3BxjFD19

retweeted_text: From the Wright brothers to astronauts John Glenn, whose birthday we celebrate today, and Neil Armstrong, Ohio’s roots in aviation and spaceflight run deep. One generation inspiring the next. Now, we're ready to send the next generation back to the #Moon—to stay. #Apollo50th https://t.co/t5LwKBOGiV

full_text: Pleased to announce that I’ll be heading down to the border today with a large bipartisan group of colleagues. The situation on our Southern border is as bad as it gets, and it’s important that we commit to working together to solve this crisis. It’s truly the only way!

Representing Ohio's 16th congressional district, Gonzalez also was a standout wide receiver for the Ohio State University Buckeyes and the NFL's Indianapolis Colts. Thanks for visiting us, Rep. Gonzalez. https://t.co/KbHlj8hcVs

full_text: My grandparents came to this country from Cuba because they believed in the strength of our constitution and our values. I came to Congress to work in a collaborative way with members across the aisle, and I encourage my colleagues to join me in that endeavor. My door is open. https://t.co/F1TJkBG5w6

O-H-I-O!! Ohio Congressman and former Ohio State football player Anthony Gonzalez invited his former Buckeye head football coach Jim Tressel to join him at President Donald Trump's 2nd State of the Union.

full_text: Excited to be joined at my first #SOTU by my wife, Elizabeth, and my former football coach and longtime mentor @JimTressel5. Jim has always encouraged me to go where I thought I could be the most useful. For me, that was Congress. Proud to share this moment with him today. https://t.co/75auCeRNFy
